data.name: label12.Text
data.value:
Chemistry performs a wide variety of tests using the most current technology. It is defined as the scientific study of matter and the various compounds of the elements as it relates to the human body. Common tests analyzed in the chemistry laboratory are glucose, cholesterol, BUN, creatinine, potassium, liver and heart enzymes, thyroid tests and hormone tests, and PSA.
The Department of Chemistry is committed to fostering a respectful workplace culture. We strive to cultivate a safe, inclusive, fair environment where our staff, faculty, researchers and students can thrive as they advance new chemical frontiers through research, innovation, collaboration and scholarship.

data.name: label1.Text
data.value:
In cytology, a skilled cytotechnologist examines human cells under the microscope, looking for early signs of cancer and other diseases. The most common type of specimen processed in the Cytology department is the Pap smear.
LTD cytology department provides a comprehensive cytology service to many clients including the NHS and independent sector. The department employs a dynamic workforce of highly trained scientists and laboratory support staff who work closely with pathologists to provide a high quality cervical and diagnostic cytology service.
HSL cytology works closely with other departments to support clinical trial studies. Continuous improvement and staff development is key to the cytology service.

data.name: label4.Text
data.value:
Hematology is the study of blood, blood morphology and blood diseases. Hematologists count and classify blood cells into different categories. Coagulation is the study of the clotting activity of blood.
LTD hematologists are experts in treating blood cancers and non-cancerous blood disorders. From the most common to incredibly rare hematologic diseases, hematology specialists at LTD use the latest technology and information to work with you to diagnose your condition.
LTD hematologists collaborate with other experts across virtually every medical and surgical specialty to individualize your care plan to your specific needs.

data.name: label6.Text
data.value:
Microbiology is the study of microorganisms including algae, bacteria, fungi, protozoa and viruses. Any bodily fluid or tissue can be cultured for infectious disease. Once bacteria grows in culture, it can be tested against many different antibiotics to find the most effective for fighting the infection while limiting opportunities for antibiotic resistance.
The Department of Microbiology at LTD brings together a variety of biomedical researchers united by the common goal of understanding the complex relationship between viral, bacterial, or parasitic pathogens and the human host. Ongoing research also focuses on several important areas of biomedical science, including the molecular basis of disease, cancer biology, and immunology.
Our research facilities include individual and shared laboratory spaces that make it easier for investigators to work with researchers in other departments and institutes.
